        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Deu 12:17",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deu 12:17",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". And to confirm this opinion, (though I would not lay too great a stress upon criticisms,) yet I cannot but observe that this tithing is spoken of only as the people’s act here, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Deu 26:12",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deu 26:12",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and the Levites are not at all mentioned in either place as receivers or takers of them, but only as partakers of them together with the owners, and therefore they are so severely charged here upon their consciences, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "thou shalt truly tithe all thine increase, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " because the execution of this was left wholly to themselves, whereas the first tithes were received by the Levites, who therefore are said ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
